# ovh_cloud_project_storage_tagging

Manages tags on an existing S3-compatible storage container without owning the bucket lifecycle.

Use this resource when the bucket is managed by another team or another Terraform state and you only need to control its tags. It is backed by the same `PUT /cloud/project/{serviceName}/region/{regionName}/storage/{name}` endpoint as the bucket resource, but writes only the `tags` field.

~> **Note:** This resource will clear all existing tags when destroyed. It is not safe to use both `ovh_cloud_project_storage_tagging` and the `tags` attribute of `ovh_cloud_project_storage` on the same bucket simultaneously.

